{"type":"spell","name":"The Treacherous Cloak","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":1,"range":{"value":"sight"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell uses a target’s clothes against him, twisting them into cords that then strangle the target for as long as the caster keeps concentrating.\nUsing the deprivation rules in Ars Magica Fifth Edition, page 180, the target must make a Stamina check every 5 rounds. Additionally, the target can attempt a Strength + Athletics stress roll against the caster’s Dexterity + Finesse Simple roll in order to break the grip of the clothes. If the character is being helped, use the highest Strength + Athletics score and add 1 for each other person helping.\nThe target can attempt a Brave Personality Trait roll against an Ease Factor of 9 in order to perform an action other than attempting to free himself from the grip of his own clothes.\nThe caster must, as usual, succeed in Concentration rolls each round.","source":"MoH","page":100,"indexKey":"the-treacherous-cloak","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.hFKzloSp1Sol0R53","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"hFKzloSp1Sol0R53","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Repair Cracks and Tears","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":2,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell allows a magus to heal cracks and tears in the parchment and leather of a book. It is a comparatively expensive way to repair books, so it is only used when the covenant lacks skilled craftsmen, or on books of such historical significance that their owners prefer they are not repaired by human hands. For example, if one of the holographic diaries of Bonisagus is damaged, it is repaired in this way, rather than by having a scribe create a replacement page, because it preserves the handwriting of the Founder.","source":"Cov","page":99,"indexKey":"repair-cracks-and-tears","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.hIp1zOAzevrPhrHB","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"hIp1zOAzevrPhrHB","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Creeping Oil","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"aq"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"voice"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"<p>Saturates a porous material with flammable oil. When casting this spell, you make a flicking motion with your index finger and thumb, as if propelling something at the target. A dot of oil appears on the target after the spell is finished, and slowly spreads over the target, saturating enough cloth to cover a person. If used on a person's clothes and ignited, the oil does +12 damage the first round, +6 the second, and +0 the third.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"creeping-oil","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"KelpTheShark"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/aq.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-aquam.Item.QlZxnFiDk4eKIPU4","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":1729835678720,"modifiedTime":1729835799650,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"U1PQp4E5HVBU8pTj","_id":"hZVHK92XMzUFesRG","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"The Beast Remade","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":10,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":true,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"<p lang=\"en-US\" style=\"line-height: 100%; margin-top: 0.21cm; margin-bottom: 0cm\">Gives one land beast a human form, though its intellect remains the same. Some feature of the animal is retained in the human form. A former dog might have an exceptionally hairy human body, and a former cat might let loose an occasional \"meow.\" Once transformed, the beast is disoriented for a while before it becomes used to its new body.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"the-beast-remade","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.i0vIFB4U2Ry2cmXX","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"i0vIFB4U2Ry2cmXX","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Books that Scream in Pain","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"room"},"complexity":0,"enhancingRequisite":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell allows the magus to check every book in a room for a physical or historical property. The name of the spell comes from the habit of an early librarian at Durenmar of making the books in the collection cry out if they were damaged, but the sigil of the caster determines the appearance of the spell’s signal. The spell’s Herbam requisite allows it to detect words in the books, provided they have a plant-based ink or binding agent, like gum arabic.","source":"Cov","page":100,"indexKey":"books-that-scream-in-pain","targetSize":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.ipPfIMYW8vX6XwW4","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ipPfIMYW8vX6XwW4","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Shiver of the Lycanthrope","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":4,"range":{"value":"personal"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"touch"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"<p lang=\"en-US\" style=\"line-height: 100%; margin-top: 0.21cm; margin-bottom: 0cm\">You feel a sudden shiver if you are touching a person or beast that is actually a lycanthrope. Variants of this spell detect other types of shapechanger, but not Bjornaer with Heartbeasts.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"shiver-of-the-lycanthrope","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"Yves Stadler"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.jG7sAuFcqAxQM3Ue","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"jG7sAuFcqAxQM3Ue","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Mighty Torrent of Water","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"aq"},"baseLevel":10,"range":{"value":"voice"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"<p>A 3-foot-diameter jet of water sprays from your outstretched arms towards your target. The target of this gusher of water takes +10 damage and must make a Strength + Size stress roll against an Ease Factor of 9 or be sent flying back.</p><p class=\"ArsMagicaText\">Marbaid of Flambeau's wizard's sigil is connected to his obsession with blood. In his version of the spell the target is hit by a gush of blood, and the stains do not go away until sunrise/sunset. This does not require a requisite, as it is a purely cosmetic effect.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"mighty-torrent-of-water","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"KelpTheShark"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/aq.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-aquam.Item.9GfKDukVbqmEgigH","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":1729835678720,"modifiedTime":1729835799659,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"U1PQp4E5HVBU8pTj","_id":"jblUJYi6SOl8enK7","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"A Day’s Worth of Spinning","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"group"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"One of the first spells taught to Petalichus by his mater, this spell cleans, cards, and spins a whole fleece, or a bale of cotton or flax, into thread in a matter of moments. If dye is available when the spell is cast, the thread can be dyed as the caster directs. A Herbam casting requisite is required for plant-based cloth.\nThis is an Average task for a mundane spinner, so the caster must make a Perception + Finesse (precision) + stress die roll against an Ease Factor of 12 (Craft Ease Factor 9 + 3 for using Craft Magic).\nFailing the roll results in a badly spun fleece, probably with flecks of dirt still clinging to the thread. A botched roll ruins the fleece outright, though this may not be immediately apparent.\nSee Covenants, page 49 for more on Rego Craft Magic.","source":"MoH","page":100,"indexKey":"a-days-worth-of-spinning","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.kITHxV40WWKr9PD5","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"kITHxV40WWKr9PD5","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
