{"type":"spell","name":"Ward Against the Beasts of Legend","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":1,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"ring"},"target":{"value":"circle"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"<p lang=\"en-US\" style=\"line-height: 100%; margin-top: 0.21cm; margin-bottom: 0cm\">No magical beast whose Magic Might is equal to or less than the level can affect anyone within the Circle or, if it is within the Circle, affect those outside. When a magus is making this and most other wards, a common gesture employed is the Fig Sign. The magus balls his or her right hand into a fist, placing the thumb between the index and middle fingers. A magus traveling to Italy should be warned that this sign is a deadly insult in that country.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"ward-against-the-beasts-of-legend","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":true,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"Yves Stadler"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.qN4KKohJxml8TG5e","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"qN4KKohJxml8TG5e","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"The Fur That Turns Blades","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"personal"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"targetSize":1,"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell causes Lexora’s fur to appear dappled with golden patches, as if in bright sunlight, and it grows warm to the touch. She becomes far more resistant to weapons, teeth or claws, but her fur remains supple, giving 4-3 protection with no load penalty. She usually casts this before going hunting or if expecting trouble.","source":"Through the Aegis","page":43,"indexKey":"the-fur-that-turns-blades","enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.qWRQFkQeul10yfnl","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"qWRQFkQeul10yfnl","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Subtle Taste of Poison and Purity","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"aq"},"baseLevel":4,"range":{"value":"personal"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"taste"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"<p>You can taste all of the properties of any liquid or mixture of liquids. Unlike <em>Touch of the Pearls,</em> you can use this sense on any number of liquids during the duration of the spell, but you must taste the liquids in question.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"subtle-taste-of-poison-and-purity","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"KelpTheShark"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/aq.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-aquam.Item.UsGog0iGg71XoD2M","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":1729835678720,"modifiedTime":1729835799721,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"U1PQp4E5HVBU8pTj","_id":"qqBIa0wooFHC7PcU","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Woolen Steed of Araby","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":1,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":4,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Imbues a woolen rug or animal pelt with the power of flight. A person sitting on the rug is lifted along with it, and the caster may make Intelligence + Finesse rolls to change direction or speed. The Ease Factor is related to current speed — Ease Factor 6 for walking pace, Ease Factor 12 at moderate speed, Ease Factor 15 at maximum speed of forty miles an hour. (Note that these Ease Factors are higher than for Mercury's Winged Sandals due to the increased difficulty of moving an object rather than oneself directly). The rug can only support the caster and his clothes; he can have no more than one point of Encumbrance or else the spell cannot lift him. The passenger is not protected from falling off the flying rug, so impressive aerial maneuvers are not recommended, nor is flying through strong winds.\nThe extra magnitudes have been added to this spell by analogy with the Rego Corpus guidelines.","source":"TME","page":111,"indexKey":"woolen-steed-of-araby","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.qqF9dC4GbXMw270x","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"qqF9dC4GbXMw270x","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Dressing the Human Form in Wool","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell crafts a single woolen garment from either raw fleeces or from spun wool. This spell is suitable for producing a cotte, cyclas, ganache, bliaut, cappa, or chausses (see the Clothing of the Thirteenth Century insert). A Finesse roll is necessary to determine the success of the craft magic; the Ease Factor is 12 if raw fleece is employed, or 9 if the base material is spun wool. The clothes produced are of standard quality; increase the Ease Factor for particularly fine or complex craft. If the Finesse roll fails, the caster is left with a useless mess of wool. Creating a fabric of a different color than the raw material requires a supply of appropriate dye, but does not change the Ease Factor. Julia typically uses this spell to manufacture clothes out of the magical cloth that she makes (see Enchanted Items, later). She does not have a spell that directly creates mundane clothing of wool due to the difficulty (it would be a similar spell to Sturdy Mantle of the Traveler, earlier). Instead, it is much easier to simply create fleeces (see Shearing the Unseen Flock, later) and then craft them into clothing with this spell. This spell employs the Level 3 Rego Animal guideline on page 50 of Covenants', “treat and process items made of animal products.”","source":"MoH","page":57,"indexKey":"dressing-the-human-form-in-wool","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.r1ZTiYrACImlP0AN","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"r1ZTiYrACImlP0AN","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"To See as Others See","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"arc"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"enhancingRequisite":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":true},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell allows a magus to read the thoughts of an animal, and give it directions. This allows the magus to indirectly sense the animal’s location, using it as a spy. The magus’s perceptions are filtered through the mind of the animal, so they focus on those stimuli that the animal finds most vivid. Dogs find smell vivid, so the magus’s perceptions, when using a dog, will focus on odiferous substances. A magus reading the mind of a magpie finds that they fixate on reflective surfaces.","source":"HoH:TL","page":139,"indexKey":"to-see-as-others-see","targetSize":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.rHW1wvZAn4PM0rv4","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"rHW1wvZAn4PM0rv4","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Touch of the Pearls","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"aq"},"baseLevel":4,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"<p>Tells you whether a liquid you hold or touch is poisonous, just as a pearl sometimes does. Safer than <em>Subtle Taste of Poison and Purity,</em> as you don't have to taste the possibly poisonous liquid.</p><p class=\"ArsMagicaText\">In Verdan of Ex Miscellanea's version of the spell, poisonous liquids turn a faint green. According to his sigil, all his spells involve the color green.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"touch-of-the-pearls","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"KelpTheShark"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/aq.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-aquam.Item.gzZGB7SuFCoqgO9n","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.4","createdTime":1729835678720,"modifiedTime":1729835799732,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"U1PQp4E5HVBU8pTj","_id":"sERSNzHofA4UbcBh","sort":0}
